it may be ascribed to a variety of causes including the presence\nof small zero-point offsets between our abundances and those used to construct\nthe calibrations or to the choice of the set of theoretical isochrones. The\nconclusions above are supported by the analysis of literature data for a larger\nnumber of Kepler targets. [Abridged]\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 Nov 2020 15:07:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-10"}
